    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Overview\nWhen daily 9 AM triggers, this workflow finds and win-backs inactive customers:\n\n1. Fetch WooCommerce orders from last 2 years\n2. Aggregate last paid order per customer and calculate days since\n3. Filter customers inactive 90+ days\n4. Process in batches of 10\n5. Build unique 15 percent coupon valid 30 days\n6. Create coupon via API with one retry\n7. Send personalized win-back email\n8. Log result to Google Sheets\n9. Alert ops on failures via Gmail\n10. Send daily summary to ops",
        "height": 376,
        "width": 396,
        "color": 3
      },
      "id": "0ba1ef06-4054-4078-aec9-ee4c7c4a2306",
      "name": "Note: Overview",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -1344,
        320
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Node-by-node Purpose\n\n1. Daily 9AM Trigger\nStarts workflow every day at 9 AM\n\n2. Get Paid Orders (Last 2 Years)\nPulls WooCommerce orders from last 2 years\n\n3. API Error Alert\nEmails ops if order fetch fails\n\n4. Aggregate Last Order Per Customer\nKeeps only paid statuses and finds each customer's most recent order date\n\n5. Inactive 90+ Days?\nChecks if days since last order is 90 or more\n\n6. Process 10 Customers at a Time\nBatches customers to avoid rate limits\n\n7. Build Summary\nCounts totals for daily report after all batches\n\n8. Send Daily Summary\nEmails ops the campaign summary\n\n9. Build Coupon Payload\nCreates unique WINBACK code with 15 percent off and 30 day expiry\n\n10. Create Coupon (Attempt 1)\nCalls WooCommerce API to create coupon\n\n11. Wait Before Retry\nPauses before second attempt\n\n12. Create Coupon (Attempt 2)\nRetries coupon creation once\n\n13. Tag Coupon Failed\nMarks customer when coupon creation fails twice\n\n14. Send Win-Back Email\nSends personalized email with coupon code\n\n15. Tag Success\nMarks successful coupon and email\n\n16. Tag Email Failed\nMarks when email send fails\n\n17. Log Result\nAppends result to Google Sheets WinBackLog\n\n18. Needs Alert?\nChecks if status is not success\n\n19. Failure Alert\nEmails ops about coupon or email failure\n\n20. Rejoin Loop\nReturns to batch processor for next customer",
        "height": 964,
        "width": 488,
        "color": 2
      },
      "id": "5906382f-05ce-4699-89c7-cedb20caff2e",
      "name": "Note: Node-by-node",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        2832,
        96
      ]
    }
